{"type":"text","timestamp":1775858335112,"sessionID":"ses_28698f613ffezy8v7A1tWucgIy","part":{"id":"prt_d7967b852001SMapzXX2oAk883","messageID":"msg_d7967a7cf0011WMWrXe9XOVgnh","sessionID":"ses_28698f613ffezy8v7A1tWucgIy","type":"text","text":"I understand now. The `.sdd_prompt.md` is asking to write a proposal for **AR-015 — PicoD 命令执行 API** following the style of AR-011 (the JWT authentication proposal). There's already a proposal at `changes/AR-015/proposal.md`, but based on the prompt, I should create a more detailed proposal following the AR-011 format with:\n\n- Purpose\n- Scope  \n- Impact Analysis\n- Alternatives Considered\n\nLet me create the updated proposal:","time":{"start":1775858335110,"end":1775858335110}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775858396922,"sessionID":"ses_28698f613ffezy8v7A1tWucgIy","part":{"id":"prt_d7967bd89001hy7c8LSVf4gP56","messageID":"msg_d7967a7cf0011WMWrXe9XOVgnh","sessionID":"ses_28698f613ffezy8v7A1tWucgIy","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_14e9bdbbd6c04a98ac027c37","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-015: PicoD Command Execution API\n\n## Purpose\n\nThis proposal implements the PicoD command execution API for the `pkg/picod` module in the AgentCube project. The goal is to:\n\n1. **Secure Command Execution** - Execute commands within controlled sandbox environments with proper isolation\n2. **Resource Limit Enforcement** - Enforce CPU, memory, time, and output size limits on command execution\n3. **Output Capture and Streaming** - Capture stdout/stderr with optional streaming for long-running commands\n4. **Cancellation Support** - Enable command cancellation via context for graceful termination\n5. **Security Hardening** - Implement security validations to prevent privilege escalation and command injection\n\nThis implementation builds upon the sandbox infrastructure established in AR-012 and provides the execution engine for code interpreters and agent runtimes.\n\n## Scope\n\n**Module:** `pkg/picod`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M\n\nThis AR covers:\n\n- **In scope:**\n  - Core `PicoD` struct and initialization (`picod.go`)\n  - Command execution logic with resource limits (`executor.go`)\n  - Resource limit configuration and enforcement (`limits.go`)\n  - Output capture and streaming (`output.go`)\n  - Security validations and sandboxing (`security.go`)\n  - Unit tests with mocked executors\n  - Integration tests with real command execution\n  - Configuration via environment variables\n\n- **Out of scope:**\n  - Container runtime integration (covered in AR-005, AR-009)\n  - Network namespace manipulation\n  - User namespace management\n  - Filesystem isolation beyond chroot/workspace jail\n  - Distributed command execution\n  - PicoD HTTP daemon (covered in `code-execution/` specs)\n\n## Current State Analysis\n\n### Existing Sandbox Infrastructure\n\nThe current system has sandbox management infrastructure:\n\n1. **Sandbox Manager** (`pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox/`):\n   - Creates and manages sandbox pods\n   - Handles lifecycle (create, update, delete)\n   - Supports warm pool for pre-provisioned sandboxes\n\n2. **CodeInterpreter CRD** (`pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go`):\n   - Defines `CodeInterpreterSpec` with image, command, args, env, resources\n   - Supports `AuthMode` enum (`picod` or `none`)\n   - Default image: `volcanosh/picod:latest`\n\n3. **Workload Manager**:\n   - Handles `CodeInterpreter` resources\n   - Creates underlying sandbox pods\n   - Injects `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` when `AuthMode=picod`\n\n### Gaps Identified\n\n1. **No unified execution API** - Command execution logic is scattered or non-existent\n2. **No resource limit enforcement** - No programmatic way to enforce CPU/memory/time limits\n3. **No output streaming** - Cannot stream output for long-running commands\n4. **No security hardening** - Missing input validation and sandboxing at the API level\n5. **No cancellation support** - Cannot gracefully cancel running commands\n\n### PicoD Context\n\nPer `code-execution/design.md` and `code-execution/spec.md`:\n- PicoD is an HTTP daemon that runs commands inside a configurable workspace jail\n- Exposes health endpoint with JWT (RSA)-protected APIs\n- CLI flags: `-port` (default 8080), `-workspace` (default: current working directory)\n- Server uses `ReadHeaderTimeout` of 10 seconds\n\n## Proposed Changes\n\n### 1. Core PicoD Structure (`picod.go`)\n\n```go\n// PicoD represents a command execution sandbox\ntype PicoD struct {\n    sandboxID    string\n    workDir      string\n    limits       *ResourceLimits\n    securityOpts *SecurityOptions\n    logger       klog.Logger\n}\n\n// Option is a functional option for PicoD\ntype Option func(*PicoD)\n\n// New creates a new PicoD instance\nfunc New(sandboxID string, opts ...Option) *PicoD\n\n// WithWorkDir sets the working directory\nfunc WithWorkDir(dir string) Option\n\n// WithLimits sets resource limits\nfunc WithLimits(limits *ResourceLimits) Option\n\n// WithSecurityOpts sets security options\nfunc WithSecurityOpts(opts *SecurityOptions) Option\n\n// WithLogger sets the logger\nfunc WithLogger(logger klog.Logger) Option\n```\n\n### 2. Resource Limits (`limits.go`)\n\n```go\n// ResourceLimits defines execution resource limits\ntype ResourceLimits struct {\n    // Timeout is the maximum execution duration\n    Timeout time.Duration\n    \n    // MaxCPU is the maximum CPU cores (e.g., 0.5, 1.0)\n    MaxCPU float64\n    \n    // MaxMemory is the maximum memory in bytes\n    MaxMemory int64\n    \n    // MaxOutputSize is the maximum output size in bytes\n    MaxOutputSize int64\n    \n    // MaxProcesses is the maximum number of processes\n    MaxProcesses int\n}\n\n// DefaultResourceLimits returns default resource limits\nfunc DefaultResourceLimits() *ResourceLimits\n\n// Validate validates resource limits\nfunc (l *ResourceLimits) Validate() error\n```\n\n### 3. Security Options (`security.go`)\n\n```go\n// SecurityOptions defines security settings for command execution\ntype SecurityOptions struct {\n    // UID is the user ID to run commands as\n    UID int\n    \n    // GID is the group ID to run commands as\n    GID int\n    \n    // Capabilities is the list of allowed capabilities\n    Capabilities []string\n    \n    // ReadOnlyFS makes the filesystem read-only\n    ReadOnlyFS bool\n    \n    // NoNetwork disables network access\n    NoNetwork bool\n    \n    // AllowedCommands is an optional allowlist of command paths\n    AllowedCommands []string\n}\n\n// DefaultSecurityOpts returns default security options\nfunc DefaultSecurityOpts() *SecurityOptions\n\n// Validate validates security options\nfunc (o *SecurityOptions) Validate() error\n```\n\n### 4. Command Execution API (`executor.go`)\n\n```go\n// Command represents a command to execute\ntype Command struct {\n    // Path is the command path\n    Path string\n    \n    // Args are the command arguments\n    Args []string\n    \n    // Env is the environment variables\n    Env []string\n    \n    // Dir is the working directory\n    Dir string\n    \n    // Stdin is the standard input\n    Stdin io.Reader\n    \n    // Stdout is the standard output (optional, captured if nil)\n    Stdout io.Writer\n    \n    // Stderr is the standard error (optional, captured if nil)\n    Stderr io.Writer\n}\n\n// CommandResult represents the result of command execution\ntype CommandResult struct {\n    // ExitCode is the process exit code\n    ExitCode int\n    \n    // Stdout is the captured standard output\n    Stdout []byte\n    \n    // Stderr is the captured standard error\n    Stderr []byte\n    \n    // Duration is the execution duration\n    Duration time.Duration\n    \n    // OOMKilled indicates if the process was killed due to OOM\n    OOMKilled bool\n    \n    // Timeout indicates if the command timed out\n    Timeout bool\n}\n\n// Run executes a command and waits for completion\nfunc (p *PicoD) Run(ctx context.Context, cmd *Command) (*CommandResult, error)\n\n// Start starts a command without waiting\nfunc (p *PicoD) Start(ctx context.Context, cmd *Command) (*Process, error)\n\n// Process represents a running process\ntype Process struct {\n    // PID is the process ID\n    PID int\n    \n    // Wait waits for the process to complete\n    Wait() (*CommandResult, error)\n    \n    // Kill sends a signal to the process\n    Kill(signal os.Signal) error\n}\n```\n\n### 5. Output Streaming (`output.go`)\n\n```go\n// OutputHandler handles streaming output\ntype OutputHandler interface {\n    // OnStdout is called when stdout data is available\n    OnStdout(data []byte)\n    \n    // OnStderr is called when stderr data is available\n    OnStderr(data []byte)\n    \n    // OnComplete is called when execution completes\n    OnComplete(result *CommandResult)\n}\n\n// RunWithStreaming executes a command with streaming output\nfunc (p *PicoD) RunWithStreaming(ctx context.Context, cmd *Command, handler OutputHandler) (*CommandResult, error)\n```\n\n### 6. Security Validation (`security.go`)\n\n```go\n// ValidateCommand validates a command for security\nfunc ValidateCommand(cmd *Command, opts *SecurityOptions) error\n\n// IsPathSafe checks if a path is within the allowed workspace\nfunc IsPathSafe(path, workDir string) bool\n\n// DropPrivileges drops privileges to the specified UID/GID\nfunc DropPrivileges(uid, gid int) error\n\n// SetResourceLimits applies resource limits to the current process\nfunc SetResourceLimits(limits *ResourceLimits) error\n```\n\n### 7. Configuration\n\n#### Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Required | Default | Notes |\n|----------|----------|---------|-------|\n| `PICOD_WORKDIR` | No | `/tmp/picod` | Base working directory |\n| `PICOD_DEFAULT_TIMEOUT` | No | `30s` | Default command timeout |\n| `PICOD_MAX_MEMORY` | No | `128Mi` | Default memory limit |\n| `PICOD_MAX_CPU` | No | `1.0` | Default CPU limit |\n| `PICOD_MAX_OUTPUT_SIZE` | No | `10MB` | Default output size limit |\n| `PICOD_MAX_PROCESSES` | No | `10` | Default process limit |\n\n### 8. Error Handling\n\n```go\n// ExecutionError represents an execution error\ntype ExecutionError struct {\n    // Type is the error type\n    Type ExecutionErrorType\n    \n    // Message is the error message\n    Message string\n    \n    // Underlying is the underlying error\n    Underlying error\n}\n\ntype ExecutionErrorType string\n\nconst (\n    ExecutionErrorTimeout    ExecutionErrorType = \"timeout\"\n    ExecutionErrorOOM        ExecutionErrorType = \"oom\"\n    ExecutionErrorCancelled  ExecutionErrorType = \"cancelled\"\n    ExecutionErrorSecurity   ExecutionErrorType = \"security\"\n    ExecutionErrorResource   ExecutionErrorType = \"resource\"\n    ExecutionErrorExec       ExecutionErrorType = \"exec\"\n)\n```\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Dependencies\n\n| Package | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|\n| `context` | Command cancellation and timeouts |\n| `os/exec` | Command execution primitives |\n| `syscall` | Process management and signals |\n| `k8s.io/klog/v2` | Structured logging |\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` | SandboxInfo type definitions |\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` | Type definitions |\n\n### Affected Components\n\n1. **Sandbox Manager** (`pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox/`): Will use PicoD for command execution within sandboxes\n2. **Workload Manager** (`pkg/workloadmanager/`): Will invoke PicoD APIs for job execution\n3. **Code Interpreter** (standalone daemon): Will use PicoD execution logic\n4. **Security Module**: Will configure security policies for command execution\n5. **Monitoring System**: Will collect metrics from command execution\n\n### Backward Compatibility\n\n- This is a new module with no existing API surface\n- No breaking changes to existing components\n- Configuration via environment variables and programmatic API\n- Existing `CodeInterpreter` CRD already references PicoD image\n\n### Risk Assessment\n\n| Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |\n|------|------------|--------|------------|\n| Command injection | Low | High | Input validation, allowlist-based command selection |\n| Resource exhaustion | Medium | High | Enforce strict CPU/memory/time limits |\n| Privilege escalation | Low | Critical | Run as non-root, drop capabilities, use namespaces |\n| Output buffer overflow | Low | Medium | Stream large outputs, enforce size limits |\n| Zombie processes | Medium | Low | Proper process reaping, signal handling |\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### Alternative 1: Use Existing Library (e.g., go-execute, bazel-remote)\n\n**Approach**: Leverage existing command execution libraries\n\n**Pros**:\n- Less code to maintain\n- Battle-tested implementations\n- Community support\n\n**Cons**:\n- May not meet specific security requirements for sandboxed execution\n- Additional dependency management overhead\n- Less control over resource limit enforcement\n- May not support Kubernetes-native patterns\n\n**Decision**: Implement custom solution for full control over security and limits, and better integration with AgentCube architecture.\n\n### Alternative 2: Shell-based Execution\n\n**Approach**: Execute commands via `/bin/sh -c`\n\n**Pros**:\n- Simple implementation\n- Shell features (pipes, redirection) available\n- Familiar syntax\n\n**Cons**:\n- Security risks (shell injection attacks)\n- Harder to control resource limits accurately\n- Additional attack surface\n- Non-deterministic behavior across shells\n\n**Decision**: Use direct execve-style execution for better security and control.\n\n### Alternative 3: Container-based Execution\n\n**Approach**: Spawn a new container for each command\n\n**Pros**:\n- Strong isolation\n- Built-in resource limits via cgroups\n- Clean environment per command\n\n**Cons**:\n- High overhead (container startup latency)\n- Requires container runtime access\n- Complex orchestration\n- Overkill for simple command execution\n\n**Decision**: Use process-level isolation with proper limits for lower latency; container isolation is handled at the sandbox pod level (AR-005).\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n1. **TestPicoD_Run_Success**: Basic command execution\n2. **TestPicoD_Run_Timeout**: Command exceeds timeout\n3. **TestPicoD_Run_OOM**: Command exceeds memory limit\n4. **TestPicoD_Run_Cancelled**: Context cancellation\n5. **TestPicoD_OutputCapture**: Stdout/stderr capture\n6. **TestPicoD_SecurityValidation**: Invalid commands rejected\n7. **TestPicoD_ResourceLimits_Validate**: Resource limit validation\n8. **TestPicoD_SecurityOpts_Validate**: Security options validation\n9. **TestPicoD_WithOptions**: Functional options pattern\n10. **TestPicoD_ExecutionErrorTypes**: Error type classification\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n1. **TestPicoD_Integration_FullLifecycle**: Full execution flow\n2. **TestPicoD_Integration_Concurrent**: Multiple concurrent commands\n3. **TestPicoD_Integration_ResourceLimits**: Verify limits are enforced\n4. **TestPicoD_Integration_Streaming**: Output streaming functionality\n5. **TestPicoD_Integration_SignalHandling**: Process signal handling\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `PicoD` struct implements all required methods\n- [ ] Resource limits are enforced (timeout, CPU, memory, output size)\n- [ ] Output capture works correctly (stdout, stderr, exit code)\n- [ ] Cancellation via context is supported\n- [ ] Security validations prevent dangerous operations\n- [ ] Streaming output is supported\n- [ ] All unit tests pass\n- [ ] Integration tests pass\n- [ ] Code coverage >= 80%\n- [ ] Documentation includes usage examples\n- [ ] Error types are properly classified and documented\n\n## References\n\n- Sandbox Infrastructure: `changes/AR-012/proposal.md`\n- Session Storage: `changes/AR-013/proposal.md`\n- Valkey Storage: `changes/AR-014/proposal.md`\n- PicoD Spec: `code-execution/spec.md`\n- PicoD Design: `code-execution/design.md`\n- Client-Go: `deployment/client-go.md`\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/AR-015-proposal.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/validation.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":46,"character":5},"end":{"line":46,"character":26}},"severity":3,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/gopls/internal/analysis/unusedfunc"},"source":"unusedfunc","message":"function \"validateContainerSpec\" is unused","tags":[1]},{"range":{"start":{"line":166,"character":5},"end":{"line":166,"character":26}},"severity":3,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/gopls/internal/analysis/unusedfunc"},"source":"unusedfunc","message":"function \"validateNetworkPolicy\" is unused","tags":[1]},{"range":{"start":{"line":248,"character":5},"end":{"line":248,"character":26}},"severity":3,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/gopls/internal/analysis/unusedfunc"},"source":"unusedfunc","message":"function \"validateLifecycleHook\" is unused","tags":[1]}],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":31,"character":1},"end":{"line":31,"character":19}},"severity":3,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/gopls/internal/analysis/unusedfunc"},"source":"unusedfunc","message":"var \"localSchemeBuilder\" is unused","tags":[1]}]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/AR-015-proposal.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/AR-015-proposal.md","time":{"start":1775858396905,"end":1775858396918}}}}
